subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. Body elongate, brown to dark brown, shiny (
Fig. 2A
); clypeal emargination deep but not reaching the base of the teeth, rounded and wide; lateral margin strongly convex and produced, forming a tooth-like projection; pronotal posterior corners in obtuse angle (
Fig. 2B
); basal apophysis of metacoxa produced; metatibia weakly or not carinate along the inner margin; superior tooth of a tarsal claw slightly longer than the inferior, distance between teeth shorter than the inferior tooth; pygidium with sparse bristles throughout (
Fig. 2
D–E); ventrites with abundant bristles (
Fig. 2C
); in males protarsomere II as long as it is wide; parameres lyre shaped; ventral surface visible in dorsal view, concave (
Fig. 2F
).
